{
  "stem": "25381.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Whatever they had-- whatever we had-- the gold or silver, or the good clothes, or the furs, or whatever, or diamonds, we had to bring it to them.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then they'll-- they'll let us, you know, survive, to live.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we did everything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then-- and then-- so we did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then we had to go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they were-- Ukrainian had already became soldiers, that they helped work with the German.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Polish boys, the young ones, they became-- you know, they volunteered.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They worked with Germans.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because the Germans, when they came, they promised them that they were going to give them-- when-- when the Russians came in 1939 and 1940, they took away the land from the people.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That everybody had a piece of land and, like in the United States, for instance, they pay taxes and they pay taxes and they had their own.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they were wealthy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were middle class.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were poor class.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When the German came in, they promised the Ukrainian people, and they promised the Polish people, that they're going to give them-- it's going to be a democracy again, like it was before.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The land that the Russian took over, they're giving them back their land and they can own their own land and their own homes and everything.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they-- So how did-- so how did the rela-- did the Ukrainians then start to treat you differently, the Jewish people?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From the beginning, they were nice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From the beginning, they were nice and friendly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then, when-- when the German came and they were very-- started to be very mean and very nasty and-- and they start to take advantage of the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
